## Definition

A [[topological space]] is a _LindelÃ¶f space_ if every [[open cover]] has a [[countable cover|countable]] sub-cover.

## Examples

* Every [[compact topological space]] is LindelÃ¶f.

* Every [[second-countable topological space]] is LindelÃ¶f.

* Every [[sigma-compact topological space]] is LindelÃ¶f.

## Properties

[[regular LindelÃ¶f spaces are paracompact]]

## References

Named after [[Ernst Leonard LindelÃ¶f]].

